OL,3,CHolidaymaker glassed in bar fears
OL,4,Cbeing left blind for life
OL,6,F"They stop serving glass and bottles
OL,7,Fso there's no weapons inside, and they
OL,8,Falso have a lock out law of 12pm where
OL,9,Fthey don't let anyone in after that
OL,10,Fcertain time" Mr Syron said.
OL,12,F"Everyone who's in the building, they
OL,13,Fknow who's in there. I'd love to see
OL,14,Fit here, and I think thousands and
OL,15,Fthousands of people would as well."
OL,17,FKeone Rawiri, Matthew's fiancee, said:
OL,18,F"It is crazy that you guys don't have
OL,19,Fsome systems in place.
