OL,3,CHolidaymaker glassed in bar fears
OL,4,Cbeing left blind for life
OL,6,F"Even if it's just identifying the hot
OL,7,Fspots where these attacks keep
OL,8,Fregularly happening and putting the
OL,9,Facts in in the certain destinations.
OL,10,FThat is what we would like to see
OL,11,Fhappen."
OL,13,FMichael Kill, chief executive of the
OL,14,FNight Time Industries Association
OL,15,F"There's lots trials out there in
OL,16,Fterms of glasses that shatter so
OL,17,Fthey're not shards, bottles that do
OL,18,Fthe same, so there's a lot of work
OL,19,Fthat goes into this to ensure that we
OL,20,Fminimise any risks, but there's still
OL,21,Flots of work to do."
